  <prompt>
    Build `EntityExtractorHandler` â€” an LLM-assisted `IToolHandler` implementation per
    FR-13 that performs Named Entity Recognition (NER) with code-based validation +
    normalization. Pipeline: input text â†’ LLM structured-output call (per existing
    structured-outputs pattern in `GenericAnalysisHandler`) â†’ deterministic post-processing
    (validate confidence â‰Ą threshold, normalize casing/whitespace, deduplicate) â†’
    structured `ToolResult` with extracted entities grouped by type.

    Configurable via `sprk_analysistool.sprk_configuration`: `entityTypes` (e.g.,
    Person, Organization, Date, Money, Location, EmailAddress, PhoneNumber);
    `confidenceThreshold` (0.0â€“1.0); `normalizationRules` (case, whitespace, format);
    `modelDeployment` override (else default from `ModelSelectorOptions`).

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100 â€” implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "EntityExtractorHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/EntityExtractorHandler.cs`. Requires corresponding
    `sprk_analysistool` row with `sprk_handlerclass = "EntityExtractorHandler"`.

    LLM call uses existing OpenAI structured-outputs pattern; respects existing AI cache
    (per-tenant cache keys per ADR-014) + `ai-context` rate limit policy (per ADR-016).
    Safety pipeline (NFR-13) preserved â€” handler calls run through existing
    `SafetyPipelineMiddleware`.

    Tests use mocked `IOpenAiClient` from `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`. Cover: contract
    test + positive (text with mixed entity types â†’ structured output with correct
    grouping) + error (LLM returns invalid JSON, confidence below threshold filters out
    entity) + config-driven (different entityTypes produces different extraction sets) +
    cache test (second identical call hits cache, no LLM invoke).
  </prompt>

