  <context>
    <background>
      `EntityExtractorHandler` is the first Wave 2 LLM-assisted handler â€” used heavily
      by chat-bound "extract entities from this doc" workflows + invoice/contract analysis
      playbooks. The handler is a thin orchestration layer: prompt the LLM with a
      structured-output schema, then deterministically validate + normalize the response
      so downstream consumers (workspace widget, JPS pipeline) get clean data.

      LLM call shape mirrors `GenericAnalysisHandler` â€” same `IOpenAiClient` pattern,
      same structured-output JSON-schema constraint, same per-tenant cache keys, same
      rate-limit policy, same safety pipeline middleware chain.
    </background>
